{"type":"app","meta":{"headers":{"x-nextjs-stale-time":"300","x-nextjs-prerender":"1","x-next-cache-tags":"_N_T_/layout,_N_T_/page,_N_T_/"}},"html":"<!DOCTYPE html><!--XzaggNHwfInZzL3uil__I--><html lang=\"en\"><head><meta charSet=\"utf-8\"/><meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\"/><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/_next/static/css/e166122f274e2341.css\" data-precedence=\"next\"/><link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/_next/static/css/2145eae04d29fac3.css\" data-precedence=\"next\"/><link rel=\"preload\" as=\"script\" fetchPriority=\"low\" href=\"/_next/static/chunks/webpack-66ccd12ae1f5e9ea.js\"/><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/87c73c54-24122e7b92478d00.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/18-b339bcfc88586b9e.js\" async=\"\"></script><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/main-app-db96051a16a27532.js\" async=\"\"></script><link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\"/><link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"/><title>Auto Router</title><meta name=\"description\" content=\"Intelligent LLM routing proxy — automatically picks the best model for every request\"/><link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Sans:wght@400;500;600;700;800&amp;family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&amp;display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/polyfills-42372ed130431b0a.js\" noModule=\"\"></script></head><body><div hidden=\"\"><!--$--><!--/$--></div><div class=\"shell\"><div class=\"landing\"><nav class=\"landing-nav\"><div class=\"landing-nav-brand\"><div class=\"landing-nav-mark\">AR</div><span class=\"landing-nav-name\">Auto Router</span></div><div class=\"landing-nav-links\"><a href=\"#features\">Features</a><a href=\"#how-it-works\">How It Works</a><a href=\"/admin\">Dashboard</a><a href=\"/admin\" class=\"nav-cta\">Get Started</a></div></nav><section class=\"hero\"><div class=\"hero-badge\">OpenAI-Compatible LLM Router</div><h1>Your models. Your rules.<br/><span class=\"gradient-text\">Routed automatically.</span></h1><p class=\"hero-sub\">Define your model catalog and routing conditions once. Auto Router follows your strategy for every request — with fallbacks, thread pinning, and guardrails built in.</p><div class=\"hero-actions\"><a href=\"/admin\" class=\"hero-btn-primary\">Configure Your Router <svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"#how-it-works\" class=\"hero-btn-secondary\"><svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"currentColor\"><path d=\"M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.01 8.01 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z\"></path></svg> View Source</a></div><div class=\"hero-code\"><div class=\"hero-code-window\"><div class=\"hero-code-bar\"><div class=\"hero-code-dot\"></div><div class=\"hero-code-dot\"></div><div class=\"hero-code-dot\"></div><span>your catalog</span></div><div class=\"hero-code-body\"><span class=\"punc\">[</span>\n<!-- -->  <span class=\"punc\">{</span>\n<!-- -->    <span class=\"prop\">id</span><span class=\"punc\">:</span> <span class=\"str\">&quot;anthropic/claude-sonnet-4&quot;</span><span class=\"punc\">,</span>\n<!-- -->    <span class=\"prop\">thinking</span><span class=\"punc\">:</span> <span class=\"str\">&quot;high&quot;</span><span class=\"punc\">,</span>\n<span class=\"line-highlight\">    <span class=\"prop\">whenToUse</span><span class=\"punc\">:</span> <span class=\"str\">&quot;Complex coding, architecture, debugging&quot;</span></span>  <span class=\"punc\">}</span><span class=\"punc\">,</span>\n<!-- -->  <span class=\"punc\">{</span>\n<!-- -->    <span class=\"prop\">id</span><span class=\"punc\">:</span> <span class=\"str\">&quot;openai/gpt-4.1-mini&quot;</span><span class=\"punc\">,</span>\n<!-- -->    <span class=\"prop\">thinking</span><span class=\"punc\">:</span> <span class=\"str\">&quot;none&quot;</span><span class=\"punc\">,</span>\n<span class=\"line-highlight\">    <span class=\"prop\">whenToUse</span><span class=\"punc\">:</span> <span class=\"str\">&quot;Simple Q&amp;A, summaries, quick tasks&quot;</span></span>  <span class=\"punc\">}</span><span class=\"punc\">,</span>\n<!-- -->  <span class=\"cmt\">// ...your other models</span>\n<span class=\"punc\">]</span></div></div></div></section><div class=\"trust-bar\"><div class=\"trust-item\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M16.5 17.5H6.3a.4.4 0 01-.4-.3.4.4 0 01.2-.4l8.6-5.4a1.8 1.8 0 00.7-2.2 1.8 1.8 0 00-1.7-1.2H5.4a.2.2 0 01-.2-.2v-.6c0-.1.1-.2.2-.2h10.1a3.8 3.8 0 013.6 2.5 3.8 3.8 0 01-1.5 4.4l-1 .6\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"></path><path d=\"M19.5 14.5a2.5 2.5 0 00-2.5-2.5\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\"></path></svg>Runs on Cloudflare Workers</div><div class=\"trust-item\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><polyline points=\"4 17 10 11 4 5\"></polyline><line x1=\"12\" y1=\"19\" x2=\"20\" y2=\"19\"></line></svg>OpenAI SDK Compatible</div><div class=\"trust-item\"><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z\"></path><path d=\"M9 12l2 2 4-4\"></path></svg>Self-Hosted &amp; Private</div><div class=\"trust-item\"><svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"currentColor\"><path d=\"M8 0C3.58 0 0 3.58 0 8c0 3.54 2.29 6.53 5.47 7.59.4.07.55-.17.55-.38 0-.19-.01-.82-.01-1.49-2.01.37-2.53-.49-2.69-.94-.09-.23-.48-.94-.82-1.13-.28-.15-.68-.52-.01-.53.63-.01 1.08.58 1.23.82.72 1.21 1.87.87 2.33.66.07-.52.28-.87.51-1.07-1.78-.2-3.64-.89-3.64-3.95 0-.87.31-1.59.82-2.15-.08-.2-.36-1.02.08-2.12 0 0 .67-.21 2.2.82.64-.18 1.32-.27 2-.27.68 0 1.36.09 2 .27 1.53-1.04 2.2-.82 2.2-.82.44 1.1.16 1.92.08 2.12.51.56.82 1.27.82 2.15 0 3.07-1.87 3.75-3.65 3.95.29.25.54.73.54 1.48 0 1.07-.01 1.93-.01 2.2 0 .21.15.46.55.38A8.01 8.01 0 0016 8c0-4.42-3.58-8-8-8z\"></path></svg>Open Source</div></div><section class=\"landing-section\"><div class=\"section-label\">The Idea</div><h2 class=\"section-heading\">You already know which model is best. Encode it.</h2><p class=\"section-desc\">You know Claude is better for code and GPT is faster for simple tasks. But implementing that logic at runtime — with fallbacks, thread continuity, and cost awareness — is a different problem entirely.</p><div class=\"problem-grid\"><div class=\"problem-card\"><div class=\"problem-icon red\">✕</div><h3>Routing logic in app code</h3><p>Model-selection ternaries scattered across your codebase. Every new model means another branch, another deploy.</p></div><div class=\"problem-card\"><div class=\"problem-icon amber\">⚠</div><h3>No fallback on failure</h3><p>A provider goes down and your users get 500s. You hardcoded one model — there’s no plan B unless you build one.</p></div><div class=\"problem-card\"><div class=\"problem-icon orange\">↑</div><h3>Context lost between turns</h3><p>Even if you route well on the first message, continuations land on a different model. KV caches are wasted and conversations break.</p></div></div></section><section class=\"landing-section\" id=\"how-it-works\"><div class=\"section-label\">How It Works</div><h2 class=\"section-heading\">Configure once. Route every request.</h2><p class=\"section-desc\">You define your model catalog with guidance on when to use each model. The router’s LLM classifier reads every incoming prompt and matches it to the right model from <em>your</em> list.</p><div class=\"flow-container\"><div class=\"flow-step\"><div class=\"flow-marker\"><div class=\"flow-number\">01</div><div class=\"flow-line\"></div></div><div class=\"flow-content\"><h3>Define your model catalog</h3><p>List the models you want available. For each one, describe when it should be used, its strengths, and its capabilities. This is your routing “constitution.”</p><div class=\"flow-code\"><span style=\"color:var(--cyan)\">anthropic/claude-sonnet-4</span>\n<!-- -->  <!-- -->thinking: high · vision: yes<!-- -->\n<!-- -->  <!-- -->use: <span style=\"color:var(--green)\">&quot;Complex code, debugging, architecture&quot;</span>\n\n<span style=\"color:var(--cyan)\">openai/gpt-4.1-mini</span>\n<!-- -->  <!-- -->thinking: none · vision: no<!-- -->\n<!-- -->  <!-- -->use: <span style=\"color:var(--green)\">&quot;Simple Q&amp;A, summaries, translations&quot;</span></div></div></div><div class=\"flow-step\"><div class=\"flow-marker\"><div class=\"flow-number\">02</div><div class=\"flow-line\"></div></div><div class=\"flow-content\"><h3>Write your routing instructions</h3><p>Give the classifier plain-language rules. “Prefer Claude for code.” “Use the cheapest model for simple questions.” “Never use models without thinking for math.” The classifier follows your instructions.</p><div class=\"flow-code\"><span style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\"># Routing Instructions</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-primary)\">- Use Claude for any coding or architecture task</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-primary)\">- Use GPT-4.1-mini for simple questions and chat</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-primary)\">- Always prefer thinking models for math/logic</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-primary)\">- If the user sends an image, pick a vision model</span></div></div></div><div class=\"flow-step\"><div class=\"flow-marker\"><div class=\"flow-number\">03</div><div class=\"flow-line\"></div></div><div class=\"flow-content\"><h3>Deploy and every request follows your rules</h3><p>Point your OpenAI SDK at the router, set <code class=\"code\">model: &quot;auto&quot;</code>. The classifier reads each prompt, picks the model from your catalog that best fits your instructions, and proxies the request. Thread pinning, fallbacks, and guardrails happen automatically.</p><div class=\"flow-code\"><span style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">// your app code — nothing changes</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--indigo)\">const</span> res = <span style=\"color:var(--indigo)\">await</span> client.chat.completions.<span style=\"color:#67e8f9\">create</span>(<!-- -->{<!-- -->\n<!-- -->  <!-- -->model: <span style=\"color:var(--green)\">&quot;auto&quot;</span>,<!-- -->\n<!-- -->  <!-- -->messages,<!-- -->\n<!-- -->}<!-- -->);<!-- -->\n\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-muted)\">// response headers tell you what happened</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--cyan)\">x-router-model-selected</span>: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4<!-- -->\n<span style=\"color:var(--cyan)\">x-router-request-id</span>: router_a1b2c3d4</div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"landing-section\" id=\"features\"><div class=\"section-label centered\">Features</div><h2 class=\"section-heading centered\">You set the strategy. The router handles the rest.</h2><p class=\"section-desc centered\">Model selection, fallbacks, thread management, and circuit breaking — all driven by the catalog and rules you define.</p><div class=\"features-grid\"><div class=\"feature-cell\"><div class=\"feature-icon-row\"><div class=\"feature-dot cyan\"></div><h3>Custom Model Catalog</h3></div><p>Define exactly which models are available, with metadata like thinking level, vision support, and natural-language guidance on when to use each one.</p></div><div class=\"feature-cell\"><div class=\"feature-icon-row\"><div class=\"feature-dot indigo\"></div><h3>Natural-Language Rules</h3></div><p>Write routing instructions in plain English. The LLM classifier reads your rules alongside the prompt and picks the model that fits.</p></div><div class=\"feature-cell\"><div class=\"feature-icon-row\"><div class=\"feature-dot green\"></div><h3>Thread Stickiness</h3></div><p>Once a model is selected for a conversation, it stays pinned. Agent tool-call loops never switch mid-chain. Caches are preserved.</p></div><div class=\"feature-cell\"><div class=\"feature-icon-row\"><div class=\"feature-dot amber\"></div><h3>Routing Profiles</h3></div><p>Create named strategies like <code class=\"code\">auto-cheap</code> or <code class=\"code\">auto-coding</code> that override the catalog, default model, and instructions.</p></div><div class=\"feature-cell\"><div class=\"feature-icon-row\"><div class=\"feature-dot cyan\"></div><h3>Circuit Breakers</h3></div><p>Three triggers — error rate, fallback rate, latency spike — automatically disable degraded models and recover after cooldown.</p></div><div class=\"feature-cell\"><div class=\"feature-icon-row\"><div class=\"feature-dot indigo\"></div><h3>Full Observability</h3></div><p>Every routing decision is stored with the classifier’s confidence, signals, and fallback chain. Query any request by ID to see exactly why.</p></div></div></section><section class=\"landing-section\"><div class=\"section-label\">Your Configuration</div><h2 class=\"section-heading\">Everything lives in the dashboard. Not in your code.</h2><p class=\"section-desc\">Change models, update routing rules, add profiles — all from the admin UI. No deploys required. Your app just sends <code class=\"code\">model: &quot;auto&quot;</code> and the router reads your latest config.</p><div class=\"compare\"><div class=\"compare-pane\"><div class=\"compare-header before\">✘ Without Auto Router</div><div class=\"compare-body\"><span class=\"del\">const model = task === &#x27;code&#x27;</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  ? &#x27;anthropic/claude-sonnet-4&#x27;</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  : task === &#x27;math&#x27;</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  ? &#x27;openai/o3&#x27;</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  : task === &#x27;vision&#x27;</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  ? &#x27;openai/gpt-4o&#x27;</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  : &#x27;openai/gpt-4.1-mini&#x27;;</span>\n<!-- -->\n<span class=\"del\">try {</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  result = await call(model, prompt);</span>\n<span class=\"del\">} catch {</span>\n<span class=\"del\">  result = await call(FALLBACK, prompt);</span>\n<span class=\"del\">}</span>\n<!-- -->\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-muted);font-style:italic\">// new model? edit code. redeploy.</span></div></div><div class=\"compare-pane\"><div class=\"compare-header after\">✔ With Auto Router</div><div class=\"compare-body\"><span class=\"add\">const res = await client.chat.completions.create({</span>\n<span class=\"add\">  model: &quot;auto&quot;,</span>\n<span class=\"add\">  messages: [{ role: &quot;user&quot;, content: prompt }],</span>\n<span class=\"add\">});</span>\n<!-- -->\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-muted);font-style:italic\">// model catalog + routing rules live in</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-muted);font-style:italic\">// the dashboard. update anytime.</span>\n<span style=\"color:var(--text-muted);font-style:italic\">// no code changes. no redeploys.</span></div></div></div></section><section class=\"landing-section\"><div class=\"section-label\">Routing Profiles</div><h2 class=\"section-heading\">One router, many strategies.</h2><p class=\"section-desc\">Create named profiles that act as virtual model names. Each profile can override the model catalog, routing instructions, and defaults — so different parts of your app get different routing behavior from the same endpoint.</p><div class=\"profiles-row\"><div class=\"profile-preview\"><div class=\"profile-preview-id\">auto-cheap</div><p class=\"profile-preview-desc\">Restrict the catalog to low-cost models. Great for internal tools, batch jobs, and simple chat.</p><span class=\"profile-tag cyan\">filtered catalog</span><span class=\"profile-tag indigo\">cost-first rules</span></div><div class=\"profile-preview\"><div class=\"profile-preview-id\">auto-coding</div><p class=\"profile-preview-desc\">Only high-thinking models. Custom instructions that prefer Claude for code and o3 for algorithms.</p><span class=\"profile-tag cyan\">thinking models only</span><span class=\"profile-tag indigo\">code-first rules</span></div><div class=\"profile-preview\"><div class=\"profile-preview-id\">auto-support</div><p class=\"profile-preview-desc\">Customer-facing tier. Fast models with guardrails. Blocklist anything experimental.</p><span class=\"profile-tag cyan\">fast defaults</span><span class=\"profile-tag indigo\">strict blocklist</span></div></div></section><section class=\"bottom-cta\"><h2>Define your routing strategy in minutes.</h2><p>Open source. Self-hosted on Cloudflare. Add your models, write your rules, and start routing.</p><div class=\"bottom-cta-actions\"><a href=\"/admin\" class=\"hero-btn-primary\">Open Dashboard <svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"><path d=\"M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"#how-it-works\" class=\"hero-btn-secondary\">Read the Docs</a></div></section><footer class=\"landing-footer\"><div class=\"landing-footer-left\">Auto Router — open-source LLM routing proxy</div><div class=\"landing-footer-right\"><a href=\"/admin\">Dashboard</a><a href=\"#how-it-works\">Docs</a><a href=\"#features\">Features</a></div></footer></div><!--$--><!--/$--></div><script src=\"/_next/static/chunks/webpack-66ccd12ae1f5e9ea.js\" id=\"